Wiring

Collect the doc page URLs your site actually serves (same slugs as your MDX routes), then pass them as knownPageUrls:

`import { createFumadocsSourceTargetResolver } from "opendetail-fumadocs";

const resolveSourceTarget = createFumadocsSourceTargetResolver([
"/docs",
"/docs/quickstart",
// …
]);
`

Pair with renderNextSourceLink from opendetail-next in a Next app so resolved targets render as next/link where appropriate.

Route handler

The scaffolded route is a thin wrapper:

`import { createNextRoute } from "opendetail-next";

export const { POST, runtime } = createNextRoute();
`

Or wire the handler yourself:

`import { createNextRouteHandler } from "opendetail-next";

export const runtime = "nodejs";
export const POST = createNextRouteHandler();
`

Requirements

Node.js 18+Route on the Node.js runtime (not Edge) for the default adapterOPENAI_API_KEY set where the handler runs.opendetail/index.json present after build

createNextRouteHandler accepts the same options as createOpenDetail (CreateOpenDetailOptions) when you need custom cwd, indexPath, or client injection.

Basic usage

`import { useOpenDetail } from "opendetail-react";

const assistant = useOpenDetail({
transport: {
  endpoint: "/api/opendetail",
},
});
`

HTTP client

Use createOpenDetailClient when you want NDJSON streaming without the hook.

`import { createOpenDetailClient } from "opendetail-react";

const client = createOpenDetailClient({
endpoint: "/api/opendetail",
});

await client.submit(
{ question: "How do I install this?" },
{
  onEvent(event) {
    console.log(event);
  },
  onStatusChange(status) {
    console.log(status);
  },
}
);
`

Create an assistant

`import { createOpenDetail } from "opendetail";

const assistant = createOpenDetail();
`

Then:

`const result = await assistant.answer({
question: "How do I configure base_path?",
});
`

answer() returns text, model, sources, images, fallback. stream() adds a ReadableStream<Uint8Array>.
